Cam::

She had been zigging and zagging through out the forest. She played 
and dodged shadows.  She was fine tuning her camoflage skills and 
making herself appear and disappear through out the flora and fauna 
in the forest. She started to skip down the hillside and chased a few 
small birds through the forest. She laughed and giggled. Played and 
smiled. Not a care in the world. At least, not untill she fell into 
an energon cage. She was housted into th tree tops and bounded around 
in the cage as it shook around untill it settled. She lay on the 
bars, swinging high above the ground. SHe shook from fright. 

Meanwhile, back in Hydras's base, the perimeter alarms were going 
off.
